Nguyen Xuan Phuc elected Vietnamese Prime Minister
HANOI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese parliament on Thursday elected Nguyen Xuan Phuc to become the country's new Prime Minister.
With voting result of 446 "yes" votes out of 490 valid ballots cast by the National Assembly (NA) deputies, Phuc was elected to be Vietnam's new cabinet chief at the ongoing 11th session of the 13th NA in capital Hanoi.
Phuc was elected to replace Nguyen Tan Dung, who was relieved from duty of Vietnamese Prime Minister on Wednesday afternoon.
HANOI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The National Assembly (NA) of Vietnam on Saturday elected Tran Dai Quang as the country's president in capital Hanoi.
Quang has been elected and sworn in as the president with 452 "yes" votes out of 481 valid ballots at the ongoing 11th session of the 13th NA. Full story
HANOI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- National Assembly (NA) of Vietnam on Thursday elected Nguyen Thi Kim Ngan as the country's first female house speaker in capital Hanoi.
Ngan has been elected and sworn in as the NA Chairperson with 472 "yes" votes out of 481 valid ballots, at the ongoing 11th session of the 13th NA. Full story